race.comment: STREAK OF WINNING (2) resumes from a spell and is having his first outing under new trainer Mark Currie. Just missed in a 70 at the Sunshine Coast when last seen and is proven fresh. Has a low gate and a handy 2kg claim. On song he will take plenty of beating. VIALE (5) led and deserved her easy CL1 win here and will carry just 52kg this grade with the claim. Draws well and she won't have to improve much to fight out the finish. IN NO DOUBT (4) resumes and was last seen winning a 58 here comfortably. That stacks up and he's trialled well. May be more forward this time around and has to be kept safe. PERFECT MISSION (1) has her second outing for Campton and we are likely to see more.
